  "title": "Quality Assurance Engineer (Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Manage the full spectrum of Quality Assurance and Quality Control activities, including equipment buy‑off (IBO and CBO) requirements and timely closure of internal and external CARS.</li><li>Continuously review and update QA systems, workflows, and documentation; spearhead improvement initiatives to drive performance beyond compliance with standards.</li><li>Drive supplier quality performance through audits, qualification, and re‑certification of vendors, supporting the company’s supply chain development efforts.</li><li>Compile weekly and monthly QA reports, ensuring clear communication of quality performance and improvement actions across teams.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Diploma in Mechanical, Production, or Mechatronics Engineering.</li><li>At least 3 years of <strong>QA experience in a manufacturing environment.</strong></li><li>Proficient in metrology tools and techniques (e.g., <strong>Vernier Caliper, Micrometer, Height & Depth Gauge, Profile Projector, Gauge Block, Smart Scope</strong>) and problem‑solving methods such as <strong>8D discipline, FMEA, and QC data analysis tools.</strong></li><li>Strong communication skills, detail‑oriented, proactive, and able to drive quality improvement programs independently while working effectively in a team.</li></ul><p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p><p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p><p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br />Registration: R21100996</p>",
